metadata.name: AGHAST (Terrified)
metadata.description:
I’m scared and I can hardly move 
I’m way too frightened 
Fear follows us , stalks us and controls us 
It’s all I think 
A heart pounding exaltation into realms of the unknown 
Paralyzing dilemmas of insufferable images portrayed as our own 
Strong but weak 
Happy but sad 
Sometimes feeling hopeful 
Scared a mad uncertain 
I’m way too frightened 
Not the people but the mind 
Not the answer but the question 
Have you ever watched a deer caught in the headlights look fleeing through his eyes ? 
Or a rabbit when it knows it has been seen ?
When they stop working the instant and hopes to disappear ? 
Suspended from the ability to think 
Overwhelmed and over stressed 
Traumatized and shocked in disbelief 
You watch their spirits shrivel up and die ? 
And all you could think of was 
I’m giving up 
My voice 
My story 
My sorrows and my pains
